Up until Score-P v10.0, not all libraries were linked with a proper library
version, in particular the MPI libraries. This is due to FCLINK ignoring
target-specific LDFLAGS.

While changing the affected libraries to use their own specified linker command,
a workaround used for ancient Intel MPI versions got re-activated.
This causes the MPI wrappers to not link the corresponding MPI libraries anymore,
hence causing linker errors for users during instrumentation.

Since the workaround is not needed anymore, remove the flag from all Intel MPI
platform files.

Original Author: Christian Feld (c.feld@fz-juelich.de)
Patch description: Jan Andre Reuter (j.reuter@fz-juelich.de)

diff --git a/build-config/common/platforms/compiler-mpi-intel b/build-config/common/platforms/compiler-mpi-intel
index 25bd829e1..77780d102 100644
--- a/build-config/common/platforms/compiler-mpi-intel
+++ b/build-config/common/platforms/compiler-mpi-intel
@@ -14,7 +14,6 @@ MPI_FFLAGS={FFLAGS}
 MPI_FCFLAGS={FCFLAGS}
 #MPI_LDFLAGS=
 #MPI_LIBS=
-MPILIB_LDFLAGS=-Wc,-nolinkage
 
 # # Scalasca1 settings
 # MPILIB    = -lmpi
